25","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-Dg0thBynCCo\/XZQur_fCPpI\/AAAAAAAAcWA\/svkA-kHTgeEM9J2dp434SA1uQnoGcR2OwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_4mS_wzqKo8_jaSid.png","title":"Pulled Pork","publishedAt":"2017-03-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"27 g","fat":"12 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"12 g","calories":"1121 kJ \/ 268 kcal"},"usefulItems":"serving bowl, basting brush, heatproof bowl","hintsAndTricks":["Make your own sauce following the BBQ Sauce recipe in the <i>US Basic Cookbook<\/i>. Increase spices to taste. Flavor will vary with store-bought barbeque sauces.","Meat may need further cooking before shredding due to fat content and cut of meat. Cook meat in increments of <b><strong>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/strong><b> until tender enough to break up with a fork when tested. The USDA Guidelines and National Pork Board recommend cooking to an internal temperature of at least 145°F, followed by a 3 minute rest.","Alternative shredding method: after steam cooking, break up pork into large pieces and place into mixing bowl and insert measuring cup. Shred pork <b><strong>5 sec\/\/speed 4<\/strong><b>. Transfer pork to a large serving bowl and keep warm until ready to serve."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","4h 5m","12 portions"]}